    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="874"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1137: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frazer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-23T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >May 23, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Following is translated text of note from German Minister at Guatemala to the
                    Government of El Salvador referred to in Department’s telegram No. 16 [<hi
                        rend="italic">15?</hi>]<note n="41" xml:id="d874fn41">See footnote 36, <ref
                            target="#pg_788">p. 788</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Here follows text of memorandum similar to the one presented to the Guatemalan
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs dated May 18, printed <hi rend="italic"
                    >supra.</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frazer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
